DON ADDITIONAL SAFETY REQUIREMENTS APPLICABLE TO SPECIFIED GOVERNMENTFURNISHED AMMUNITION AND EXPLOSIVE
column5:
(a) Use the clause at 5252.223-9000, DON ADDITIONAL SAFETY REQUIREMENTS APPLICABLE TO SPECIFIED GOVERNMENT FURNISHED AMMUNITION AND EXPLOSIVES, in solicitations and contracts that:

(1) contain the clause at DFARS 252.223-7002; and

(2) provide as GFM any A&E containing nitrocellulose-based propellants and/or nitrate ester-based materials (such as nitroglycerin,) or other similar A&E with a tendency to become chemically unstable over time.

NOTIFY OESRC in unsuccessful in removing clause, as ITAR would be applicable.
column6:
Negotiation Position #1 - No Explosives or Ammunition.

This clause is prescribed to be used in contracts in which the Government will be providing ammunition and explosives (A&E) containing nitrocellulose-based propellants and/or nitrate ester-based materials (such as nitroglycerin,) or other similar A&E with a tendency to become chemically unstable over time.   Virginia Tech will be receiving A&E in the performance of this effort.  Therefore, it is requested for this clause to be removed for clarity.  Thank you.
